modules.description: This module provides direct access to gperftools (tcmalloc) memory management features, allowing explicit control over memory release rates, inspection and modification of internal numeric properties, and runtime heap profiling. It works with standard memory allocation structures and exposes operations to start, stop, and dump heap profiles, as well as query and set memory behavior parameters. Concrete use cases include optimizing memory usage in long-running OCaml applications, diagnosing memory leaks through heap dumps, and tuning memory release policies for performance-critical services.
